I know as a first time mom more then 8 pounds can sound scary. But your body's got this. As long as you breath well (breath in through your nose and out through your mouth like your blowing through a straw. And I mean deep concentrated breathing) and do not clinch your fists or tense up (yes, it is possible) do your best to do those and follow what you body is telling you. My 3rd baby came before my midwife was able to get to my house. I delivered him myself with no meds and no doctor with me and my hubby caught him. Your body knows what it's doing, and most women deliver totally fine without complications. Your body will make you push. You will know your ready because it will start making you push without you really trying. You literally wont be able to hold back from pushing. The breathing that I told you about and no tensing really helps with calming down some pain during contractions either during the entire thing if your going med free or during the ones you'll experience before an epidural. When sanitizing shopping carts, keep in mind that it usually takes 20-60 seconds for the disinfectant to work after you have cleaned your cart. 2. Grab extra wipes when wiping down your cart and use these wipes for opening freezer and refrigerator doors when opening the door to select your items. 3. One of the BIGGEST things, you already know about, but for those reading this that do not, do NOT touch your face!!! PERIOD!!! Carry tissues with you for moments when you feel the need to scratch. One of the BIGGEST things, you already know about, but for those reading this that do not, do NOT touch your face!!! PERIOD!!! Carry tissues with you for moments when you feel the need to scratch. As for the Cov19 virus, I am here on the Oregon coast and I really do not think that we will be hit hard in the Pacific Northwest....at least I hope not, as I am a so called senior with autoimmune disease and lung disease, which basically means that if I catch the virus, it's all over for me. On a normal daily basis, even before this virus, I have been required to prepare as everyone is doing right now with sanitizing shopping carts, hands, etc... Here are a few good tips that my doctor gave to me prior to this recent virus. 1. When sanitizing shopping carts, keep in mind that it usually takes 20-60 seconds for the disinfectant to work after you have cleaned your cart. 2. Grab extra wipes when wiping down your cart and use these wipes for opening freezer and refrigerator doors when opening the door to select your items. 3. One of the BIGGEST things, you already know about, but for those reading this that do not, do NOT touch your face!!! PERIOD!!! Carry tissues with you for moments when you feel the need to scratch. Do NOT use your clothing as it comes in contact with possibly contaminated items. 4. Wash hands IMMEDIATELY upon returning home and again after you have put groceries away. 5. ALWAYS think CROSS-CONTAMINATION!! If someone else could have touched it in ANY way, then it has the potential to pass germs to you. I wish EVERYONE a safe existence until this bug has ran its course. I send out a VERY SPECIAL prayer to those that are seniors such as myself, and have underlying health issues that make catching this virus a matter of life and death. Please be safe and keep our great nation in prayer during this time. Schon vor diesem Virus musste ich mich täglich darauf vorbereiten, wie jeder es jetzt tut, indem ich Einkaufswagen, Hände usw. desinfiziere. Hier sind ein paar gute Tipps, die mir mein Arzt vor dem jüngsten Virus gegeben hat. 1. Wenn Sie Einkaufswagen desinfizieren, denken Sie daran, dass es normalerweise 20-60 Sekunden dauert, bis das Desinfektionsmittel wirkt, nachdem Sie den Wagen gereinigt haben. 2. Nehmen Sie zusätzliche Tücher mit, wenn Sie Ihren Einkaufswagen abwischen, und verwenden Sie diese Tücher zum Öffnen der Gefrier- und Kühlschranktüren, wenn Sie die Tür öffnen, um Ihre Waren auszuwählen. 3. Eines der größten Dinge, die Sie bereits wissen, aber für diejenigen, die das hier lesen, die es nicht wissen: Berühren Sie NICHT Ihr Gesicht!!! PERIOD!!! Waschen Sie sich sofort die Hände, wenn Sie nach Hause kommen, und nochmals, nachdem Sie Ihre Einkäufe weggeräumt haben. 5. Denken Sie IMMER an CROSS-CONTAMINATION! My 3rd baby came before my midwife was able to get to my house. I delivered him myself with no meds and no doctor with me and my hubby caught him. Your body knows what it's doing, and most women deliver totally fine without complications. Your body will make you push. You will know your ready because it will start making you push without you really trying. You literally wont be able to hold back from pushing.
